Company Overview of CU Bancorp



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
K. Brian Horton  President, Director, President of California United Bank and Director of California United Bank, CU BancorpAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships57$847,841As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. K. Brian Horton has been the President of CU Bancorp and California United Bank since December 1, 2014. Mr. Horton served as the President of 1st Enterprise Bank since February 2006. Mr. Horton served as the President of Southern Division at Mellon 1st Business Bank, N.A., since August 2004 with oversight responsibility of Orange County, South Bay and Inland Empire Regional offices. He served as Treasurer of Goodwill of Orange County from 2003 to 2004. He co-founded ... 1st Enterprise Bank in 2006. He served as Chairman of the Board of Directors of Goodwill Industries of Orange County. He has headed Southern Division of M1BB since January 2004 and served as its Executive Vice President. He joined M1BB in February 1988. He worked for First Interstate Bank of California, both in the Los Angeles Headquarters and Orange County Corporate Banking divisions. He serves as a Director of Goodwill of Orange County. He has been a Director of CU Bancorp and California United Bank since December 1, 2014. He served as a Director at 1st Enterprise Bank since February 2006. He has been active in a number of community related organizations. Mr. Horton received a Bachelor's degree in Business Administration and Finance from the University of Oregon.Read Full Background




