 Career History



President

                                    2014 - Current                


CU Bancorp


                  CU Bancorp operates as a holding company of California United Bank. It is a commercial bank, which offers banking products and services designed for small and medium-sized businesses, non-profit organizations, business owners and entrepreneurs, and the professional community. The company was founded on November 16, 2011 and is headquartered in Los Angeles, CA.                




President

                                    2014 - Current                


California United Bank


                  California United Bank provides commercial banking services. It offers deposit services, lending, international banking, online banking, treasury management, and private banking services. The firm focuses on serving small and medium-sized businesses, professionals, entrepreneurs, and non-profit organization. The company was founded by Charles Sweetman on September 30, 2004 and sis headquartered in Los Angeles, CA.                




Executive Vice President

                                    1988 - Prior                


First Business Bank (Madison, Wisconsin)


                  First Business Bank of Madison offers a full line of financial services for businesses and business owners, including commercial lending, treasury management, private banking, retirement plans, investment management services, trust services, asset based lending and equipment finance and leasing. The company was founded in March 1990 and is headquartered in Madison, WI.                




Founding Member

                                    2005 - 2014                


1st Enterprise Bank


                  1st Enterprise Bank is a full-service commercial bank, serving the banking needs of businesses and their owners throughout Southern California. The company offers a full range of credit and depository services, with special emphasis on personalized customer service, cash management services and direct access to bank decision makers. Its services include commercial, real estate and consumer loans, business and personal checking accounts, money market accounts, savings accounts and certificates of deposit, trade finance, business and personal Internet banking, and remote business deposit. The company serves Southern California entrepreneurial businesses, professional firms and nonprofit organizations, along with their owners and key managers. 1st Enterprise Bank was founded in 2006 and is headquartered in Los Angeles, CA.                




Division President

                                    Prior - 2005                


Mellon 1st Business Bank


                  Mellon 1st Business Bank provides financial services. It provides institutional asset management, mutual funds, private wealth management, operating & equipment loans, asset-based financing, credit cards, financial advisory, trust and investment services. The company is a subsidiary of Mellon Financial Corp. Mellon 1st Business Bank was founded by Joseph P. Sanford in 1981 and is headquartered in Los Angeles, CA                




Professional

                                    1983 - 1988                


First Interstate Bank


                  First Interstate Bank seeks to provide returns that meet or exceed their clients’ expectations while remaining within their risk tolerance. They carefully craft investment solutions using a disciplined multi-step process that allows their clients to implement a planned approach to investment success. First Interstate Bank offers eight different account objectives, ranging from capital preservation to all equity. These objectives represent strategies designed to meet a range of time horizons and risk tolerance levels. Each strategy is managed to achieve broad capital market diversification. These objectives include: Capital Preservation, All Fixed, Current Income, Income With Growth, Balanced, Growth With Income, Growth and All Equity.                





